PROBLEM APPROACH:
Watch a perceptron learn in real time on XOR data using the classic update rule: only misclassified points trigger updates, with no weight decay. 
Because XOR is not linearly separable, a single perceptron cannot hit 100% accuracy. 
Reach 75% accuracy to prove you understand the limitation and reveal the flag.

HINTS:
You get 16 updates per run, and correctly classified points do not change the model in the classic rule.
The learning-rate sweep is wide (0.02 through 20.0), so very high values can swing the boundary aggressively.
XOR cannot be perfectly separated by one line; 75% is the best achievable target for this setup.
Use the slider to sweep the range and watch how the decision boundary moves between misclassification updates.

